# Git Publish Gate

Agents MUST NOT publish to GitHub on their own.

## Required

- **Do not** run `git push`, `git push --force`, or any remote publish unless the user **explicitly** asks to push/publish in that message.
- Completing work or syncing artifacts does **not** imply push permission.
- Local `git commit` also requires an **explicit** user request to commit.

## When the user asks to push

1. Load skill **`edunudg-pre-push-ci`**
2. Run **`pnpm ci:local`** (full GitHub CI mirror)
3. **Automatically fix** every failure and re-run until green (or report a hard blocker — no push)
4. Only then `git push` (and only the refs the user asked for)

Skipping RLS/e2e requires the user to allow that skip in the same message.

## After local work (no push ask)

Leave changes uncommitted/unpushed. Tell the user what is ready and wait for “commit”, “push”, or “commit and push”.

## Forbidden

- Pushing to “unblock CI” without a local green `ci:local`
- Pushing knowing local CI is red
- Treating a prior push as standing permission for the next one
